casebody.data:
Jonathon TRAMPE, Respondent,
v.
DIRECTOR OF REVENUE, Appellant. No. ED 106020 Missouri Court of Appeals, Eastern District, DIVISION THREE. Filed: September 4, 2018
Motion for Rehearing and/or Transfer to Supreme Court Denied October 15, 2018
Application for Transfer Denied December 18, 2018 FOR APPELLANTS: Morgan Brewington, 301 W. High Street, P.O. Box 475, Jefferson City, Missouri 65105. FOR RESPONDENTS: Denise L. Childress, Carl M. Ward, 305 West 4 th Street Washington, Missouri 63090. Before Sherri B. Sullivan, P.J., Lawrence E. Mooney, J., and James M. Dowd, J.

ORDER

PER CURIAM

The Director of Revenue of the State of Missouri appeals the judgment of the Circuit Court of St. Louis County setting aside the Director's decision to suspend the driving privileges of Jonathon Trampe.

We affirm. Because an extended opinion would have no precedential value, the parties have been furnished with a memorandum for their information only, setting forth the reasons for this order pursuant to Rule 84.16(b).
